Then she will be chasing you.

590
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:02,960
Got it?

591
00:27:04,559 --> 00:27:05,160
That's the right way.

592
00:27:12,359 --> 00:27:13,519
Wenwen. Wenwen.

593
00:27:13,599 --> 00:27:14,519
No more singing, sweetie.

594
00:27:14,519 --> 00:27:15,400
Your grandma's here.

595
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,599
She won't like hearing that.

596
00:27:19,119 --> 00:27:20,039
Ma'am is here.

597
00:27:20,240 --> 00:27:21,119
Mr. Yu, you too.

598
00:27:21,119 --> 00:27:22,599
Welcome, everyone.

599
00:27:24,720 --> 00:27:26,119
This was all Yu Ming's idea.

600
00:27:27,960 --> 00:27:28,839
Aunt.

601
00:27:29,400 --> 00:27:30,559
You are all here.

602
00:27:31,319 --> 00:27:32,000
Ming.

603
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:33,200
Congratulations.

604
00:27:34,039 --> 00:27:35,759
Big opening day today.

605
00:27:36,519 --> 00:27:37,079
Thank you.

606
00:27:37,079 --> 00:27:37,599
Ming.

607
00:27:37,720 --> 00:27:39,400
This place does not look like a bar.

608
00:27:39,559 --> 00:27:41,039
Because it's not a bar.

609
00:27:41,079 --> 00:27:42,440
You see any alcohol here?

610
00:27:42,440 --> 00:27:43,119
Where is the alcohol?

611
00:27:43,359 --> 00:27:44,400
This is specially

612
00:27:44,400 --> 00:27:45,640
designed for families.

613
00:27:45,720 --> 00:27:46,799
The Happiness Experience Center.

614
00:27:47,000 --> 00:27:47,640
Got it?

615
00:27:47,880 --> 00:27:49,079
How is it happiness?

616
00:27:50,440 --> 00:27:51,160
Happiness

617
00:27:51,799 --> 00:27:53,400
starts with breaking a wall.

618
00:27:58,240 --> 00:27:58,680
Dad.

619
00:27:59,400 --> 00:28:00,359
What does this mean?

620
00:28:00,599 --> 00:28:02,640
You should study people's teeth more.

621
00:28:02,640 --> 00:28:04,559
Stop drawing everyone with giant fangs.

622
00:28:05,440 --> 00:28:06,240
It's telling you

623
00:28:06,359 --> 00:28:07,640
not to be so sharp-tongued,

624
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:09,319
but to choose peace and love.

625
00:28:17,480 --> 00:28:18,720
I don't even eat garlic.

626
00:28:18,839 --> 00:28:20,319
Everyone has their fate, son.

627
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,480
Too accurate.

628
00:28:21,599 --> 00:28:22,039
It means

629
00:28:22,039 --> 00:28:23,079
you should just let it go.

630
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,839
Stop following her around all day.

631
00:28:30,039 --> 00:28:31,079
Jesus.

632
00:28:31,440 --> 00:28:32,480
Here. Let me show you.

633
00:28:35,680 --> 00:28:36,599
Look how shattered mine is.

634
00:28:36,759 --> 00:28:37,759
Even more smashed than my gossip.

635
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:43,960
I'm a major shareholder, after all.

636
00:28:43,960 --> 00:28:45,039
I paid for all this.

637
00:28:45,039 --> 00:28:46,599
And all I get is "Thanks for playing"?

638
00:28:46,799 --> 00:28:48,200
How is that my fault?

639
00:28:48,240 --> 00:28:49,359
You just told your son

640
00:28:49,359 --> 00:28:50,319
everyone has their fate.

641
00:28:50,319 --> 00:28:52,000
Your fate is probably "try again."

642
00:28:52,039 --> 00:28:53,920
At least give me another hammer swing.

643
00:28:55,920 --> 00:28:56,839
Mom, you try.

644
00:28:57,039 --> 00:28:57,400
Okay.

645
00:28:57,640 --> 00:28:58,359
Let's try too.

646
00:28:58,359 --> 00:28:58,720
Smash it.

647
00:28:58,880 --> 00:28:59,319
Okay.

648
00:28:59,599 --> 00:29:00,319
Here it's.

649
00:29:02,839 --> 00:29:03,920
Let's do it.

650
00:29:16,880 --> 00:29:19,319
Its thorns hurt when they prick you.

651
00:29:20,000 --> 00:29:21,000
But inside,

652
00:29:21,839 --> 00:29:22,960
the flesh is still soft and tender.

653
00:29:40,480 --> 00:29:41,400
Congratulations!

654
00:29:44,160 --> 00:29:44,759
Yu Ming.

655
00:29:44,920 --> 00:29:46,519
What does this poop mean?

656
00:29:46,680 --> 00:29:47,960
It means

657
00:29:47,960 --> 00:29:49,359
go to the counter for tissues.

658
00:29:49,559 --> 00:29:50,880
So it's a poop coupon?

659
00:29:54,119 --> 00:29:56,680
The Eiffel Tower means Paris and Europe.

660
00:29:56,880 --> 00:29:58,400
Hanover isn't far from there.

661
00:30:41,160 --> 00:30:41,640
What?

662
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:43,000
Nothing.

663
00:30:54,160 --> 00:30:54,720
What is this?

664
00:30:55,240 --> 00:30:56,279
A penguin.

665
00:30:56,720 --> 00:30:57,480
I know it's a penguin.

666
00:30:57,480 --> 00:30:58,480
What does it supposed to mean?

667
00:30:58,599 --> 00:30:59,359
Well, penguins

668
00:30:59,359 --> 00:31:01,119
live in the polar regions.

669
00:31:01,480 --> 00:31:03,920
So it represents our attitude...

670
00:31:03,920 --> 00:31:04,759
Yu Ming.

671
00:31:05,559 --> 00:31:06,759
Go sing a song.

672
00:31:07,799 --> 00:31:08,319
Mom.

673
00:31:09,920 --> 00:31:11,480
You can talk now?

674
00:31:11,839 --> 00:31:13,119
I have held it in long enough.

675
00:31:13,519 --> 00:31:14,759
If I kept quiet any longer,

676
00:31:14,920 --> 00:31:16,799
I would forget how to speak.

677
00:31:17,200 --> 00:31:18,160
Sing a song.

678
00:31:18,359 --> 00:31:19,799
I... I said

679
00:31:19,839 --> 00:31:20,440
I wouldn't sing anymore.

680
00:31:20,440 --> 00:31:21,559
I want to hear it.

681
00:31:22,880 --> 00:31:23,440
But...

682
00:31:25,160 --> 00:31:27,079
Do I have to carry you up there?

683
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,680
Dad, come on.

684
00:31:29,079 --> 00:31:29,480
Come on.

685
00:31:29,799 --> 00:31:30,279
Go.

686
00:31:49,960 --> 00:31:51,279
I haven't sung in so long.

687
00:31:52,279 --> 00:31:53,079
I may have forgotten

688
00:31:53,079 --> 00:31:54,279
how to make a sound.

689
00:31:56,200 --> 00:31:57,000
I...

690
00:31:59,119 --> 00:32:00,279
I will sing a song

691
00:32:00,279 --> 00:32:01,920
Wenwen usually likes to sing.

692
00:32:04,240 --> 00:32:05,119
For my brother.

693
00:32:05,240 --> 00:32:06,240
And for all of you.

694
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,240
I hope my brother

695
00:32:09,319 --> 00:32:10,720
can watch over us

696
00:32:10,759 --> 00:32:11,680
from above

697
00:32:11,759 --> 00:32:13,920
and bless us happy every day.

698
00:32:14,680 --> 00:32:15,079
Yes.

699
00:32:18,960 --> 00:32:20,440
One, two, three.

700
00:32:21,920 --> 00:32:24,079
♪Facing the light,
I break through the dark♪

701
00:32:25,920 --> 00:32:28,160
♪Fearless strength is written
in my hands♪

702
00:32:30,119 --> 00:32:33,319
♪Pour me a Bloody Mary♪

703
00:32:33,599 --> 00:32:36,680
♪Drink my worries to the last drop♪

704
00:32:38,160 --> 00:32:40,519
♪Facing the light,
I break through the dark♪

705
00:32:42,200 --> 00:32:44,559
♪I shout out loud
with nothing to regret♪

706
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,039
♪In this harsh and restless world♪

707
00:32:48,039 --> 00:32:49,759
♪I hope♪

708
00:32:49,759 --> 00:32:52,759
♪All journeys lead to brighter days♪

709
00:32:54,359 --> 00:32:56,680
♪Life is full of surprises♪

710
00:32:58,519 --> 00:33:00,680
♪Snow may fall in the height of summer♪

711
00:33:02,519 --> 00:33:04,839
♪As if fate had slipped for a moment♪

712
00:33:05,079 --> 00:33:08,240
♪Yet I keep flying against the wind♪

713
00:33:08,240 --> 00:33:09,880
Fate is a funny thing.

714
00:33:10,440 --> 00:33:12,000
It's like running on a hamster wheel.

715
00:33:13,160 --> 00:33:14,160
When you are poor,

716
00:33:14,519 --> 00:33:17,759
you hope
one more spin wins you a fortune.

717
00:33:18,960 --> 00:33:20,559
But once you have money, you realize

718
00:33:21,759 --> 00:33:22,880
what is weighing you down

719
00:33:23,440 --> 00:33:26,319
is still the cage called desire.

720
00:33:27,759 --> 00:33:28,720
The weird thing is,

721
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:31,119
after all that chaos,

722
00:33:31,839 --> 00:33:34,319
the restlessness inside me

723
00:33:35,039 --> 00:33:36,119
finally quieted down.

724
00:33:37,440 --> 00:33:40,039
I can't see that monkey anymore.

725
00:33:41,680 --> 00:33:45,039
Something else has taken its place.

726
00:33:46,680 --> 00:33:49,240
Something that has calmed my heart.

727
00:33:51,039 --> 00:33:52,119
The money is gone,

728
00:33:52,839 --> 00:33:55,079
but I still have family and friends.

729
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:59,200
They are my real treasure.

730
00:34:00,799 --> 00:34:03,319
Wenwen is much more cheerful now.

731
00:34:04,480 --> 00:34:05,680
She is my wings.

732
00:34:06,680 --> 00:34:08,119
When I run wild,

733
00:34:08,920 --> 00:34:10,679
she lifts me up and lets me fly.

734
00:34:12,119 --> 00:34:13,239
And the kite string

735
00:34:13,920 --> 00:34:16,280
is always in Wen Yitong's hands.

736
00:34:17,239 --> 00:34:18,000
With her here,

737
00:34:18,599 --> 00:34:21,119
our family will never fly off course.

738
00:34:31,480 --> 00:34:33,320
The Walkman under Mom's pillow

739
00:34:33,639 --> 00:34:34,760
is no longer needed.

740
00:34:35,679 --> 00:34:38,760
(Demo "Mr. Money" by Yu Ming)
I sing to her live every day

741
00:34:39,159 --> 00:34:40,079
to help her fall asleep.

742
00:34:40,760 --> 00:34:41,519
When she sleeps well,

743
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,079
of course she recovers faster.

744
00:34:45,440 --> 00:34:48,960
As for my parents' misunderstandings
back then,

745
00:34:49,400 --> 00:34:51,199
Dad has talked to me about them.

746
00:34:51,840 --> 00:34:54,199
It was really just

747
00:34:54,320 --> 00:34:56,159
(Blood Pressure Monitor)
a problem with communication.

748
00:34:56,559 --> 00:34:59,159
But time smooths everything over.

749
00:35:00,559 --> 00:35:01,519
Their relationship

750
00:35:02,039 --> 00:35:03,559
has gone back to how it used to be.

751
00:35:04,239 --> 00:35:06,960
Ever since Mom lost her voice,

752
00:35:07,320 --> 00:35:09,880
they haven't argued once.

753
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:13,760
Dad takes her out for walks every day.

754
00:35:14,480 --> 00:35:15,519
They are so sweet together now.

755
00:35:18,840 --> 00:35:21,000
Qian Weijie may look happy.

756
00:35:22,159 --> 00:35:23,480
But since the second baby arrived,

757
00:35:23,760 --> 00:35:25,199
he's tired out every day.

758
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:28,280
He calls it pain with a side of joy.

759
00:35:33,119 --> 00:35:34,840
As for Ouyang Shiqi,

760
00:35:36,119 --> 00:35:38,039
he went abroad to find Chen Zinuo.

761
00:35:38,880 --> 00:35:40,519
He never found her.

762
00:35:41,400 --> 00:35:42,880
But he kept looking

763
00:35:43,320 --> 00:35:45,599
until he got good at another language.

764
00:35:47,760 --> 00:35:49,280
I have to admit

765
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:51,320
that kind of devotion is impressive.

766
00:35:53,679 --> 00:35:55,519
What he doesn't know

767
00:35:56,239 --> 00:35:57,440
is that Chen Zinuo

768
00:35:57,679 --> 00:36:00,719
tried to contact him after returning.

769
00:36:01,840 --> 00:36:02,960
Heartbreaking, right?

770
00:36:06,280 --> 00:36:09,119
Tiezhu and his brothers did well too.

771
00:36:09,880 --> 00:36:11,880
They built their own freight team,

772
00:36:12,400 --> 00:36:13,760
and things really took off.

773
00:36:14,880 --> 00:36:15,800
As for Liu Xinlu,

774
00:36:16,480 --> 00:36:19,519
Yitong said she left Song Youcheng.

775
00:36:20,400 --> 00:36:22,079
She found a new job

776
00:36:22,480 --> 00:36:23,880
and started over.

777
00:36:25,480 --> 00:36:26,199
So, in the end,

778
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,400
after all that trouble,

779
00:36:28,719 --> 00:36:30,000
everyone's life

780
00:36:30,639 --> 00:36:34,159
ended up better than before.

781
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:37,159
There is a rock on the southwest coast.

782
00:36:37,679 --> 00:36:39,320
The waves crashed against it for years.

783
00:36:39,840 --> 00:36:41,159
At high tide,

784
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,000
it booms like a giant drum.

785
00:36:43,159 --> 00:36:44,599
That is how the island got its name.

786
00:36:45,484 --> 00:36:49,040
(Six Months Later)

787
00:36:52,917 --> 00:36:58,003
(To a bold horse, no ditch is too wide.
To a timid heart, every step's a bump.)

788
00:37:08,360 --> 00:37:09,519
Here is the problem.

789
00:37:09,760 --> 00:37:11,199
You barely talk to the customers.

790
00:37:11,480 --> 00:37:13,000
Greeting people, seeing them off,

791
00:37:13,239 --> 00:37:15,039
I'm fine with the service part.

792
00:37:15,119 --> 00:37:16,800
My Mandarin is just not good.

793
00:37:16,800 --> 00:37:17,920
So I keep quiet.

794
00:37:18,000 --> 00:37:18,880
Besides,

795
00:37:18,880 --> 00:37:21,079
your whole business idea has problems.

796
00:37:21,159 --> 00:37:22,639
This is supposed to be for families.

797
00:37:22,719 --> 00:37:23,800
But you put bottles of liquor

798
00:37:23,800 --> 00:37:24,440
all over the place.

799
00:37:24,480 --> 00:37:26,079
Parents leave after seeing them.

800
00:37:26,159 --> 00:37:27,199
Wasn't this supposed

801
00:37:27,199 --> 00:37:28,360
to be a bar at first?

802
00:37:28,360 --> 00:37:29,960
And we have to maximize profit.

803
00:37:29,960 --> 00:37:31,400
Kids don't come out at night.

804
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:33,519
Parents spend all day with them.

805
00:37:33,519 --> 00:37:34,320
They are exhausted.

806
00:37:34,320 --> 00:37:35,400
They need a drink at night.

807
00:37:35,480 --> 00:37:36,800
Makes perfect sense.

808
00:37:36,960 --> 00:37:38,199
Then during the day,

809
00:37:38,239 --> 00:37:39,119
can you at least put up a panel

810
00:37:39,199 --> 00:37:40,480
and hide the alcohol?

811
00:37:40,880 --> 00:37:42,119
Listen.

812
00:37:42,159 --> 00:37:43,199
This is where we are right now.

813
00:37:43,360 --> 00:37:43,920
Last month,

814
00:37:44,039 --> 00:37:45,079
only eight people walked in.

815
00:37:45,199 --> 00:37:46,159
Four delivery drivers.

816
00:37:46,280 --> 00:37:47,199
Two couriers.

817
00:37:47,280 --> 00:37:48,519
And one was looking for the bathroom.

818
00:37:48,679 --> 00:37:50,119
So much for your golden zone.

819
00:37:50,239 --> 00:37:51,519
Look how well that worked.

820
00:37:51,719 --> 00:37:53,079
Why did I ever listen to you?

821
00:37:53,679 --> 00:37:54,719
I think

822
00:37:54,920 --> 00:37:56,559
our biggest problem

823
00:37:56,639 --> 00:37:58,440
is that nobody knows we exist.

824
00:37:58,519 --> 00:38:00,559
We have done basically no marketing.

825
00:38:00,840 --> 00:38:01,840
You still want to put more money in?

826
00:38:01,960 --> 00:38:03,199
More money, Yu Ming?

827
00:38:03,320 --> 00:38:04,400
You did save my life,

828
00:38:04,480 --> 00:38:05,719
but you can't drain it back out of me

829
00:38:05,760 --> 00:38:07,199
one investment at a time.

830
00:38:07,320 --> 00:38:08,800
I say we find someone

831
00:38:08,840 --> 00:38:09,760
to take over the lease.

832
00:38:09,880 --> 00:38:11,199
(Some break through their inner wall)
Cut our losses while we still can.

833
00:38:11,400 --> 00:38:12,519
(Some never find a way around it.)
My son is still little.

834
00:38:12,559 --> 00:38:13,840
He is years away from adulthood.

835
00:38:14,480 --> 00:38:15,119
Exactly.

836
00:38:15,280 --> 00:38:16,199
We waited for you

837
00:38:16,199 --> 00:38:17,119
for quite a while, too.

838
00:38:17,119 --> 00:38:18,239
It's too long.

839
00:38:19,599 --> 00:38:20,880
Then what now?

840
00:38:20,920 --> 00:38:22,679
Fine. Fine.

841
00:38:26,440 --> 00:38:27,119
All right.

842
00:38:27,199 --> 00:38:27,800
Okay.

843
00:38:29,079 --> 00:38:29,880
Guess who called.

844
00:38:30,679 --> 00:38:31,159
Who?

845
00:38:32,159 --> 00:38:33,199
That Lu guy who wanted the house.

846
00:38:33,920 --> 00:38:34,840
He is back?

847
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:36,360
Turns out,

848
00:38:36,360 --> 00:38:37,599
after seeing our house that day,

849
00:38:37,679 --> 00:38:38,559
he went drinking,

850
00:38:38,599 --> 00:38:39,639
got caught driving drunk,

851
00:38:39,719 --> 00:38:40,920
and spent six months in custody.

852
00:38:40,960 --> 00:38:42,280
That's why he disappeared.

853
00:38:43,039 --> 00:38:44,039
Poor guy.

854
00:38:44,280 --> 00:38:46,400
Then the house...

855
00:38:46,440 --> 00:38:47,960
The sale is still on, right?

856
00:38:48,000 --> 00:38:48,760
No.

857
00:38:48,760 --> 00:38:49,639
He wants

858
00:38:49,719 --> 00:38:51,000
his deposit back.

859
00:38:51,079 --> 00:38:51,840
Why?

860
00:38:52,000 --> 00:38:53,920
He says the house is too cursed for him.

861
00:38:53,960 --> 00:38:54,599
Didn't he say

862
00:38:54,599 --> 00:38:56,079
he needed more bad luck in his life?

863
00:38:56,159 --> 00:38:56,920
He said now,

864
00:38:56,920 --> 00:38:57,960
the "bad luck"

865
00:38:57,960 --> 00:38:58,679
won't work anymore.

866
00:38:58,719 --> 00:38:59,760
It's pure bad luck now.

867
00:38:59,920 --> 00:39:01,360
He said we are tough.

868
00:39:01,400 --> 00:39:02,360
We survived that place.

869
00:39:02,519 --> 00:39:03,800
So what do we do now?

870
00:39:03,800 --> 00:39:05,679
So... we give it back?

871
00:39:05,840 --> 00:39:07,360
We can't just keep it, can we?

872
00:39:07,400 --> 00:39:08,760
We should return it.

873
00:39:10,280 --> 00:39:11,239
He is such a trouble.

874
00:39:11,239 --> 00:39:12,679
That house is already hard to sell.

875
00:39:12,760 --> 00:39:14,480
We lowered the price to 3 million now.

876
